                                                                                                                                         PIV Authentication certificate



                                    Figure 1. PKI-based derived PIV credential lifecycle activities

380   The lifecycle of a derived PIV credential begins with the issuance of a derived PIV
381   credential on an approved device or authenticator associated with the applicant. This
382   may be part of the process of issuing a PIV Card or a subsequent process. Mobile devices
383   with derived PIV credentials are managed as described in [SP800-124].
384   The maintenance activities for a PKI-based derived PIV credential are the same as
385   for other X.509 public key certificates. Certificate re-key is typically used to replace

